{
  "stem": "4113.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we stayed there at that house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Then we moved to another house with a straw roof that you had to bend down to get in there, to a Jewish fellow, an orthodox Jewish fellow, who used to buy glass from us.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So we stayed at his house until the German armies marched in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "When they marched in, you know, highly motorized-- something you didn't see in the Polish army, which was mostly you know, on horses, or-- they didn't have the-- a mechanized army like the Germans did.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "When they came, it was very impressive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Here power coming in all of a sudden.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And nothing happened.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "When they first came in, it was very quiet.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We used to go out, stand around, watch them, and so on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And as soon as they marched in, my father decided with a few other people from our town to go back to see what happened.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We had my uncle Haim-- the one who said that they won't marinate me, I'm not going to go, I know Germans, they are wonderful, the most they can do is put me to work, I've worked all my life anyway-- he stayed in our house, because he lived a little bit out of town and he thought he's safer to stay right in the center, so he stayed in our apartment and he watched our place.",
      "word_count": 77
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "My father decided to go back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But instead of going back straight into my hometown, Krosno, they stopped in a little shtetl, a little tiny town, about 5 kilometers to the north of the town, to sort of find out, feel out what goes on in our town.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Now, we stayed behind in that town, Dynow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And a few days later, the SS marched in.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
